1) gather all books that you would like to sort
2) place books together in an area to sort them
3) examine all books for their titles 
4) compare the first letter in each books title, and if the first letters are the same go on to the second letter until there is a difference
5) move the books around in order based on the previous comparisons. This order is based on which title had the "smallest" letter or sequence of letters
6) Once all books have been compared and sorted alphabetically, review the order you have done to check that it is sorted correctly.
7) finalize the sorting you have done and replace the books in the same order where you need them to be

